      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MAYBE YES (2) led early but gathered in and found a bit of trouble before fading to finish a 9 length seventh (20.33) in a Grade 5 at this track. Better than latest and well worth another try. QUIRKY NACHO (8) is rarely far away but tends to find one better, placing 19 from 30 starts. Finished in the minors latest when second (19.92) at this track and may be close to breaking through. Goes very well here at the trip finding the frame in each of seven starts. Remains without a win from the draw but has been in the placings four times from six attempts. Will give a great sight again. JACOBITE THORN (1) is a consistent runner who is new to this track. Lines up here in winning form after scoring by 0.8 lengths from box two at Temora (19.05). Leading chance again. FRAME SISTER (6) was out of the frame here most recently but can atone.",
